tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown: ### [First Input Delay (FID)](https://web.dev/fid/): Measures the time from when a user first interacts with your site to the time when the browser is actually able to respond to that interaction

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown: ### [Largest Contentful Paint (LCP)](https://web.dev/lcp/): Measures the time a website takes to show the user the largest content on the screen, complete and ready for interaction

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown: ### [Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)](https://web.dev/cls/): Measures of the largest burst of layout shift scores for every unexpected layout shift that occurs during the entire lifespan of a page.

tiles.name: Markdown
tiles.markdown: ### [Time to First Byte (TTFB)](https://wp-rocket.me/google-core-web-vitals-wordpress/reduce-ttfb-server-response-times/#:~:text=engagement%20and%20retention.-,What%20is%20a%20Good%20Time%20to%20First%20Byte%20(TTFB)%3F,-Google%20recommends%20a): Measures how fast the application is repsonding to client requests. TTFB is an effective measure of back-end performance. TTFB should be less than 500 milliseconds.
